h: Siblings die in Road accident
Himachal Pradesh: Five people killed in Road accident in Dharamshala
sub_h: The accident took place at Rasehar village of Uthragran gram panchayat in Dharamshala assembly constituency.

h: In HP, 23% fatalities during accidents caused by collision
3 Punjab residents killed, 1 injured as vehicle falls into gorge in Shimla
sub_h: Three people from Punjab were killed while another was injured after the vehicle ferrying them rolled off road and fell into a 900 meter gorge in Shimla on Monday night.

h: Himachal Pradesh: 3 dead, 1 injured as pillar falls on tipper vehicle in Mandi
sub_h: Three persons were killed and one injured after a cement pillar fell on a tipper vehicle at a construction site in Himachal Pradesh's Mandi district on Tuesday morning.

h: Himachal Pradesh: 7 tourists from UP and Delhi killed, 10 injured as vehicle falls into gorge in Kullu
sub_h: As many as seven people were killed and 10 others suffered injuries as a tempo traveller fell into a gorge in Kullu district of Himachal Pradesh on Sunday evening.

h: In Himachal Pradesh, crash barriers installed only on 1.36% roads
sub_h: A critical analysis of “rolled down” accidents in last 5 years carried by Himachal Pradesh Police has revealed that these accidents happen due to lack of “crash barriers” along the roads.

h: Newly-wed couple from UP killed in accident in Manali
sub_h: A honeymoon trip to Himachal Pradesh ended in tragedy for a newly married couple from Uttar Pradesh. Rohit Kaushik (23) and Mansi (23) were killed after their jeep collided with a truck on Kullu-Manali national highway late Thursday night.

h: 4 die, 25 hurt in 2 HP Road accidents
sub_h: Himachal Pradesh has reported four deaths and 25 injuries in two Road accidents in the last 24 hours. In Shimla, four people died and another was injured on Friday evening, while in Solan, 24 schoolchildren were hurt.

h: 15 injured as bus skids off and rolls down road in Shimla
sub_h: At least 15 people suffered injuries after a bus skidded off the road near Baghar Kenchi and rolled down around 50-60 feet below the road in Shimla on Thursday.

h: 4 die, 25 hurt in 2 Himachal Pradesh Road accidents
sub_h: Himachal Pradesh has reported four deaths and 25 injuries in two Road accidents during the last 24 hours. In Shimla district's Chopal area on Friday evening, four people died and another was injured, while in Solan district, 24 schoolchildren were hurt.

h: 13 injured in Road accident in Shimla
sub_h: Shimla: Thirteen people were injured after a Himachal Road Transport Corporation bus skidded on a road near Kufri on Wednesday, an official said. The bus was going from Haridwar to Rampur. pti

h: 3 killed in Kinnaur Road accident
sub_h: Three persons were killed when the vehicle they were travelling fell into a gorge along Wangtoo-Kafnu link road in Kinnaur district of Himachal Pradesh on Monday. The ill-fated car fell into around 250-metre gorge resulting in on the spot death of three occupants.

h: 1 killed, 38 injured in Mandi Road accident
sub_h: A Himachal Road Transport Corporation (HRTC) bus driver was killed and 37 passengers, including tourists, and the conductor were injured after the vehicle collided with a mountain face near Pandoh reservoir in Mandi district of Himachal Pradesh on Monday.

h: Himachal Pradesh: 1 killed, 38 injured in Mandi Road accident
sub_h: A Himachal Road Transport Corporation (HRTC) bus driver was killed and 37 passengers, including tourists, and the conductor were injured after the vehicle collided with a mountain face near Pandoh reservoir in Mandi district of Himachal Pradesh on Monday.

h: Himachal Pradesh: Three persons killed in Chamba Road accident
sub_h: The accident took place late Saturday evening near Ghirdu on the Khadamukh-Holi road. After which the occupants of the car went missing. A massive search operation was launched by the team comprising police and personnel of Atal Bihari Mountaineering Sub Center.

h: Himachal Pradesh: Two dead, 14 hurt as bus falls into gorge in Mandi district
sub_h: The accident took place at Jhir village of Sarkaghat sub division, Mandi superintendent of police Shalini Agnihotri said.

h: Himachal Pradesh: 5 injured in two separate road mishaps
sub_h: At least five persons were injured in separate road related incidents in Shimla and Solan districts on Thursday.

h: Four killed in different Road accidents in Himachal Pradesh
sub_h: Four persons were killed in two different Road accidents in Himachal Pradesh on Wednesday. While three persons were killed in Sirmaur district after their vehicle rolled into a gorge, one person was killed and his minor son was injured in Kinnaur district after boulder fell on their car.

h: One dead, 15 injured as bus, truck collide inside tunnel in Himachal Pradesh
sub_h: According to police, the bus and the truck had a head-on collision inside the tunnel. While the truck driver dies, 15 passengers of the bus, including some tourists, sustained injuries. The deceased has been identified as Ganesh Kushwaha, 30, resident of Uttar Pradesh.

h: Himachal Pradesh: 9 killed, as many injured as bus falls into gorge in Chamba district
sub_h: Nine people were killed while as many were injured after a private bus fell into a gorge near Colony Morh in Tissa sub-division of Chamba district on Wednesday morning.

h: Himachal Pradesh: 20 injured in Road accident in Solan district
sub_h: Around 20 passengers were injured when an over-speeding truck loaded with apples hit a private bus from behind along the Parwanoo-Shimla national highway near Jabli in Solan district on Sunday.

h: Two dead, nine injured after vehicle falls into gorge in Shimla
sub_h: Two persons were killed and nine others suffered injuries after a vehicle (Force Max) they were travelling in veered off the road and fell into a deep gorge at Tanki Nallah along Narkanda-Baagi road in Shimla on Wednesday late evening.

h: Three killed in Road accident in Mandi
Seven dead, 1 injured as jeep falls into gorge in Himachal Pradesh's Mandi
sub_h: Seven persons were killed after a jeep they were travelling in plunged into a gorge at Pul Gharat in Mandi late Sunday night.

h: Himachal Pradesh: 4 killed as car falls into nullah in Shimla
sub_h: Four people were killed after their car fell into a 200-feet deep nullah here, police said on Friday.

h: One dead, three injured as apple laden truck fell into gorge in Shimla
sub_h: One person died and three others, including two women, sustained injuries as an apple laden truck fell into gorge in Himachal Pradesh's Shimla district on Wednesday, police said.

h: One army jawan killed, three injured in Road accident near Shimla
Himachal Pradesh: Over 95% accidents occur due to human error, says transport minister Govind Singh Thakur
sub_h: In Himachal Pradesh over 95% Road accidents are taking place due to human error. Transport minister Govind Singh Thakur informed the state assembly on Wednesday that between August 1, 2015 and August 16 this year, 12,475 s took place of which 11,859 s (95.06%) occurred due to human error while only 616 (4.94%) accidents took place on account of road conditions.

h: Himachal Pradesh: Three killed in Road accident in Rampur
sub_h: Three people were killed and one injured, On Wednesday, when a Bolero they were travelling in skidded off the road and fell into a gorge at Pedi nullah along Jeuri-Ghanvi link road in Rampur sub-division of Shimla district in Himachal Pradesh.

h: Seven killed in two traffic accidents in Himachal Pradesh
